📌 What is SSL/TLS in ELB?
    SSL (Secure Sockets Layer) / TLS (Transport Layer Security) is the technology that encrypts traffic between the user's browser and your load balancer. 
    When you add an HTTPS listener to an ALB, all traffic is encrypted in transit — the browser shows a 🔒 padlock icon.

⚙️ Step-by-Step — Add HTTPS Listener with SSL Certificate:
      Step 1 — Navigate:
          Go to AWS Console → EC2
          In the left panel → Click "Load Balancers"
          Select ELB-Demo-ALB
          Click "Listeners and Rules" tab
      Step 2 — Add Listener:
          Click "Add Listener"
          Configure
          Setting	    Value
          Protocol	    HTTPS
          Port	        443
          Default Action	Forward to → demo-tg-alb
      Step 3 — Add SSL Certificate:
          ⚠️ HTTPS requires an SSL Certificate — you must attach one before saving. There are two ways:
          Option A — Use AWS Certificate Manager (ACM) — Recommended ✅
        
          Setting	Value
          Certificate Source	ACM (AWS Certificate Manager)
          Certificate	Select existing OR request a new one
          💡 ACM provides FREE SSL certificates for domains you own. You need a registered domain name (e.g., myapp.com) to request one.
          
      Option B — Import External Certificate
     
      Setting	                Value
      Certificate Source	    Import Certificate
      Certificate Body	        Paste your .crt file content
      Private Key	            Paste your .key file content
      Certificate             Chain	Paste your CA chain (optional)
      Step 4 — Security Policy:
              Setting	            Value
              Security Policy	ELBSecurityPolicy-2016-08(default — recommended)
      💡 Security Policy controls which SSL/TLS versions and cipher suites are supported. The default policy supports TLS 1.2 and above — safe for most use cases.
      
      Step 5 — Save Listener:
              Review all settings
              Click "Add" ✅
              ⏳ Takes effect within 30–60 seconds
      
      Step 6 — Verify:
            Go back to Listeners and Rules tab
          You should now see TWO listeners:
              Listener	Port	Action
              HTTP	    80	    Forward to demo-tg-alb
              HTTPS	    443	    Forward to demo-tg-alb ✅
🔄 Best Practice — HTTP to HTTPS Redirect:
⚠️ After adding HTTPS, users who type http:// should be automatically redirected to https://. Here's how:

    Step 1 — Select the HTTP :80 Listener → Edit
    Step 2 — Change Default Action:
    Setting	        Value
    Default Action	Redirect to HTTPS
    Port	        443
    Status Code	    301 — Permanently Moved
    Click "Save" ✅

      User Browser
           │
           │  HTTPS (encrypted) 🔒
           ▼
      ELB-Demo-ALB
      (SSL Certificate installed here)
      (ALB decrypts the traffic — SSL Termination)
           │
           │  HTTP (plain) — internal traffic
           ▼
      demo-tg-alb (Target Group)
           │
           ├─────────────────────┐
           │                     │
      First Instance       Second Instance
      (EC2 — httpd)        (EC2 — httpd)
